Reasoning: The paper discusses the effectiveness of altmetrics in measuring the impact of research, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are likely sub-categories as they deal with the organization and retrieval of digital information, including research papers. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) are also possible sub-categories as they deal with the social and societal impact of technology, which includes the dissemination and evaluation of research. Finally, cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a less likely sub-category, but still possible as altmetrics may be used to evaluate the impact of software engineering research.
